climbs.name: Exiled in Sweden
climbs.fa: S. Strong, T. Michael, T. Gordon, & A. Bartlett, 12/89

content.description: Ascend the north face past three bolts on nice rock. The distance between bolts is significant; definitely not a sport route. At the third bolt go left and then back right up to the top. A direct finish above the third bolt is 5.12- (on TR).
content.protection: Three bolts and one #3 TCU in a horizontal between the second and third bolts. Medium cams and long runners to sling horns work well for an anchor. Walk off to the left (east).

climbs.name: Bulkhead Arete
climbs.fa: A. Bartlett, T. Gordon, T Michael, & S. Strong, 1989

content.description: Begin on a ledge at the base of the north face just left of the arete. Unprotected face climbing on large holds (5.8 - 5.9) gain the arete. Continue on the arete before moving onto the west face past a bolt to the top.
content.protection: Small to medium stoppers and brass plus a few small TCU's protect the arete. One bolt is located on the west face before the topout. An anchor can be made by slinging horns and supplementing with medium cams. Walk off to the east.
